  "prompt": "What is a bank branch name?",
  "response": "A bank branch name refers to the specific designation given to a physical location of a bank where customers can conduct banking transactions. This name typically includes the bank's name followed by the particular branch\u2019s identifier, which may be related to its geographic location, such as the city or neighborhood. For example, \"Chase Bank - Downtown Branch\" or \"Wells Fargo - Main Street Branch.\" Each branch may offer a range of services, including account opening, deposits, withdrawals, loans, and financial advice.",
